apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: ClusterRole
metadata:
  name: custom
rules:
- apiGroups:
  - monitoring.coreos.com
  resources:
  - servicemonitors
  - podmonitors
  verbs:
  - '*'
---
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: ClusterRole
metadata:
  name: deployment-scaler-role
rules:
- apiGroups:
  - apps
  resources:
  - deployments
  - deployments/scale
  verbs:
  - get
  - list
  - patch
  - update
- apiGroups:
  - ""
  resources:
  - pods
  verbs:
  - list
  - get
---
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: ClusterRole
metadata:
  name: flux-deployer-custom
rules:
- apiGroups:
  - helm.fluxcd.io
  - monitoring.coreos.com
  - apiextensions.k8s.io
  resources:
  - helmreleases
  - servicemonitors
  - podmonitors
  verbs:
  - '*'
---

  name: deployment-scaler-binding

  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: deployment-scaler-role
subjects:
- kind: ServiceAccount
  name: atcore
  namespace: atcore-performance
- kind: ServiceAccount
  name: sbnews
  namespace: sbnews-performance
- kind: ServiceAccount
  name: homepage
  namespace: homepage-performance
---

apiVersion: image.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v1beta1
kind: ImageUpdateAutomation
metadata:
  name: image-automation
  namespace: flux-system
spec:
  git:
    checkout:
      ref:
        branch: master
    commit:
      author:
        email: flux-auto-update@reedbusiness.com
        name: FluxBot-image-automation
      messageTemplate: "Automated image update\n\nAutomation name: {{ .AutomationObject
        }}\n\nFiles:\n{{ range $filename, $_ := .Updated.Files -}}\n- {{ $filename
        }}\n{{ end -}}\n\nObjects:\n{{ range $resource, $_ := .Updated.Objects -}}\n-
        {{ $resource.Kind }} {{ $resource.Name }}\n{{ end -}}\n\nImages:\n{{ range
        .Updated.Images -}}\n- {{.}}\n{{ end -}}  \n"
  interval: 5m0s
  sourceRef:
    kind: GitRepository
    name: flux-system
---

  09-filter-pipeline-output.conf: |-
    output {
      pipeline {
        send_to => ["output-pipeline"]
      }
    }
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: logstash-k8s-filter-config
  namespace: logging
---
apiVersion: v1
data:
  00-input-http.conf: |-
    input {
      http {
        port => 8080
        codec => "json"
      }
    }

    output {
      pipeline {
        send_to => ["filter-pipeline"]
      }
    }

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  annotations:
    service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-backend-protocol: tcp
    service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-internal: "true"
    service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-nlb-target-type: instance
    service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-scheme: internal
    service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-subnets: subnet-0d51a2aa909b1d523,subnet-0a7d104e1b322f246,subnet-0d1b6a85a4628ff58
    service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-type: external
  labels:
    app: thanos-query
    self-monitor: "true"
  name: thanos
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  loadBalancerSourceRanges:
  - 10.0.0.0/8
  ports:
  - name: thanos
    port: 10901
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: grpc
  selector:
    app.kubernetes.io/component: query
    app.kubernetes.io/name: thanos
  type: LoadBalancer

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/component: logstash
    app.kubernetes.io/name: elasticsearch-logstash
  name: logstash
  namespace: logging
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app.kubernetes.io/component: logstash
      app.kubernetes.io/name: elasticsearch-logstash
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app.kubernetes.io/component: logstash
        app.kubernetes.io/name: elasticsearch-logstash
    spec:
      containers:
      - env:
        - name: ES_HOSTS
          value: https://logs.cha.rbxd.ds
        image: artifacts.cha.rbxd.ds/icis-services/logstash:9.0.3
        name: logstash
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
          name: http-input
        - containerPort: 9600
          name: metrics
        resources:
          limits:
            cpu: 1000m
            memory: 2Gi
          requests:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 1Gi
        volumeMounts:
        - mountPath: /usr/share/logstash/config/logstash.yml
          name: logstash-config
          subPath: logstash.yml
        - mountPath: /usr/share/logstash/config/pipelines.yml
          name: pipelines-config
          subPath: pipelines.yml
        - mountPath: /usr/share/logstash/k8s-assets/input-conf
          name: k8s-input-config
        - mountPath: /usr/share/logstash/k8s-assets/filter-conf
          name: k8s-filter-config
        - mountPath: /usr/share/logstash/k8s-assets/output-conf
          name: k8s-output-config
      volumes:
      - configMap:
          items:
          - key: logstash.yml
            path: logstash.yml
          name: logstash-base-config
        name: logstash-config
      - configMap:
          items:
          - key: pipelines.yml
            path: pipelines.yml
          name: logstash-pipelines
        name: pipelines-config
      - configMap:
          name: logstash-k8s-input-config
        name: k8s-input-config
      - configMap:
          name: logstash-k8s-filter-config
        name: k8s-filter-config
      - configMap:
          name: logstash-k8s-output-config
        name: k8s-output-config
---
apiVersion: autoscaling/v2
kind: HorizontalPodAutoscaler
metadata:
  name: logstash-hpa
  namespace: logging
spec:
  behavior:
    scaleDown:
      policies:
      - periodSeconds: 300
        type: Percent
        value: 20
      selectPolicy: Min
      stabilizationWindowSeconds: 600
    scaleUp:
      policies:
      - periodSeconds: 60
        type: Pods
        value: 2
      selectPolicy: Max
      stabilizationWindowSeconds: 300
  maxReplicas: 9
  metrics:
  - resource:
      name: cpu
      target:
        averageUtilization: 90
        type: Utilization
    type: Resource
  minReplicas: 3
  scaleTargetRef:
    apiVersion: apps/v1
    kind: Deployment
    name: logstash
---
apiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1
kind: ServiceMonitor
metadata:
  labels:
    monitoring-platform: icis-monitoring
    namespace: logging
  name: logstash
  namespace: logging
spec:
  endpoints:
  - interval: 15s
    path: /
    port: metrics
    scrapeTimeout: 10s
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: logstash
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  annotations:
    cert-manager.io/cluster-issuer: vault-issuer
    lnrs.io/zone-type: private
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/backend-protocol: HTTP
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/proxy-body-size: 8m
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/proxy-buffer-size: 64k
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-ciphers: ALL:!aNULL:!EXPORT56:+HIGH:+MEDIUM:+LOW:+SSLv2:+EXP
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: loki-gateway
    app.kubernetes.io/name: loki-gateway
  name: loki-gateway
  namespace: logging
spec:
  ingressClassName: icis-nginx-ingress
  rules:
  - host: loki-eks-5a.cha.eu-west-1.dev
    http:
      paths:
      - backend:
          service:
            name: loki-gateway
            port:
              name: http-metrics
        path: /loki/api/v1/
        pathType: ImplementationSpecific
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - loki-eks-5a.cha.eu-west-1.dev
    secretName: loki-eks-5a.cha.eu-west-1.dev
---

apiVersion: v1
data:
  metrics-config.yml: |-
    # Inspired by kafka-connect rules
    # https://github.com/prometheus/jmx_exporter/blob/master/example_configs/kafka-connect.yml
    # See https://github.com/prometheus/jmx_exporter for more info about JMX Prometheus Exporter metrics
    lowercaseOutputName: true
    lowercaseOutputLabelNames: true
    rules:
      #kafka.connect:type=app-info,client-id="{clientid}"
      #kafka.consumer:type=app-info,client-id="{clientid}"
      #kafka.producer:type=app-info,client-id="{clientid}"
      - pattern: 'kafka.(.+)<type=app-info, client-id=(.+)><>start-time-ms'
        name: kafka_$1_start_time_seconds
        labels:
          clientId: "$2"
        help: "Kafka $1 JMX metric start time seconds"
        type: GAUGE
        valueFactor: 0.001
      - pattern: 'kafka.(.+)<type=app-info, client-id=(.+)><>(commit-id|version): (.+)'
        name: kafka_$1_$3_info
        value: 1
        labels:
          clientId: "$2"
          $3: "$4"
        help: "Kafka $1 JMX metric info version and commit-id"
        type: GAUGE
      #kafka.producer:type=producer-topic-metrics,client-id="{clientid}",topic="{topic}"", partition="{partition}"
      #kafka.consumer:type=consumer-fetch-manager-metrics,client-id="{clientid}",topic="{topic}"", partition="{partition}"
      - pattern: kafka.(.+)<type=(.+)-metrics, client-id=(.+), topic=(.+), partition=(.+)><>(.+-total|compression-rate|.+-avg|.+-replica|.+-lag|.+-lead)
        name: kafka_$2_$6
        labels:
          clientId: "$3"
          topic: "$4"
          partition: "$5"
        help: "Kafka $1 JMX metric type $2"
        type: GAUGE
      #kafka.producer:type=producer-topic-metrics,client-id="{clientid}",topic="{topic}"
      #kafka.consumer:type=consumer-fetch-manager-metrics,client-id="{clientid}",topic="{topic}"", partition="{partition}"
      - pattern: kafka.(.+)<type=(.+)-metrics, client-id=(.+), topic=(.+)><>(.+-total|compression-rate|.+-avg)
        name: kafka_$2_$5
        labels:
          clientId: "$3"
          topic: "$4"
        help: "Kafka $1 JMX metric type $2"
        type: GAUGE
      #kafka.connect:type=connect-node-metrics,client-id="{clientid}",node-id="{nodeid}"
      #kafka.consumer:type=consumer-node-metrics,client-id=consumer-1,node-id="{nodeid}"
      - pattern: kafka.(.+)<type=(.+)-metrics, client-id=(.+), node-id=(.+)><>(.+-total|.+-avg)
        name: kafka_$2_$5
        labels:
          clientId: "$3"
          nodeId: "$4"
        help: "Kafka $1 JMX metric type $2"
        type: UNTYPED
      #kafka.connect:type=kafka-metrics-count,client-id="{clientid}"
      #kafka.consumer:type=consumer-fetch-manager-metrics,client-id="{clientid}"
      #kafka.consumer:type=consumer-coordinator-metrics,client-id="{clientid}"
      #kafka.consumer:type=consumer-metrics,client-id="{clientid}"
      - pattern: kafka.(.+)<type=(.+)-metrics, client-id=(.*)><>(.+-total|.+-avg|.+-bytes|.+-count|.+-ratio|.+-age|.+-flight|.+-threads|.+-connectors|.+-tasks|.+-ago)
        name: kafka_$2_$4
        labels:
          clientId: "$3"
        help: "Kafka $1 JMX metric type $2"
        type: GAUGE
      #kafka.connect:type=connector-task-metrics,connector="{connector}",task="{task}<> status"
      - pattern: 'kafka.connect<type=connector-task-metrics, connector=(.+), task=(.+)><>status: ([a-z-]+)'
        name: kafka_connect_connector_status
        value: 1
        labels:
          connector: "$1"
          task: "$2"
          status: "$3"
        help: "Kafka Connect JMX Connector status"
        type: GAUGE
      #kafka.connect:type=task-error-metrics,connector="{connector}",task="{task}"
      #kafka.connect:type=source-task-metrics,connector="{connector}",task="{task}"
      #kafka.connect:type=sink-task-metrics,connector="{connector}",task="{task}"
      #kafka.connect:type=connector-task-metrics,connector="{connector}",task="{task}"
      - pattern: kafka.connect<type=(.+)-metrics, connector=(.+), task=(.+)><>(.+-total|.+-count|.+-ms|.+-ratio|.+-avg|.+-failures|.+-requests|.+-timestamp|.+-logged|.+-errors|.+-retries|.+-skipped)
        name: kafka_connect_$1_$4
        labels:
          connector: "$2"
          task: "$3"
        help: "Kafka Connect JMX metric type $1"
        type: GAUGE
      #kafka.connect:type=connector-metrics,connector="{connector}"
      #kafka.connect:type=connect-worker-metrics,connector="{connector}"
      - pattern: kafka.connect<type=connect-worker-metrics, connector=(.+)><>([a-z-]+)
        name: kafka_connect_worker_$2
        labels:
          connector: "$1"
        help: "Kafka Connect JMX metric $1"
        type: GAUGE
      #kafka.connect:type=connect-worker-metrics
      - pattern: kafka.connect<type=connect-worker-metrics><>([a-z-]+)
        name: kafka_connect_worker_$1
        help: "Kafka Connect JMX metric worker"
        type: GAUGE
      #kafka.connect:type=connect-worker-rebalance-metrics
      - pattern: kafka.connect<type=connect-worker-rebalance-metrics><>([a-z-]+)
        name: kafka_connect_worker_rebalance_$1
        help: "Kafka Connect JMX metric rebalance information"
        type: GAUGE
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  labels:
    app: strimzi
  name: connect-metrics
  namespace: icis-event-streaming

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: prometheus-elasticsearch-exporter
  namespace: icis-monitoring
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: prometheus-elasticsearch-exporter
  strategy:
    rollingUpdate:
      maxSurge: 1
      maxUnavailable: 0
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: prometheus-elasticsearch-exporter
    spec:
      containers:
      - command:
        - /bin/elasticsearch_exporter
        - --es.uri=$(ELASTICSEARCH_URL)
        - --es.timeout=60s
        - --es.indices
        - --es.ssl-skip-verify
        - --es.all
        env:
        - name: ELASTICSEARCH_URL
          valueFrom:
            secretKeyRef:
              key: ELASTICSEARCH_URL
              name: elasticsearch-vars
        image: artifacts.cha.rbxd.ds/docker_images_proxy/prometheuscommunity/elasticsearch-exporter:latest
        name: prometheus-elasticsearch-exporter
        ports:
        - containerPort: 9114
          name: http
        resources:
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 128Mi
          requests:
            cpu: 25m
            memory: 64Mi
        securityContext:
          capabilities:
            drop:
            - SETPCAP
            - MKNOD
            - AUDIT_WRITE
            - CHOWN
            - NET_RAW
            - DAC_OVERRIDE
            - FOWNER
            - FSETID
            - KILL
            - SETGID
            - SETUID
            - NET_BIND_SERVICE
            - SYS_CHROOT
            - SETFCAP
          readOnlyRootFilesystem: true
      restartPolicy: Always
      securityContext:
        fsGroup: 10000
        runAsGroup: 10000
        runAsNonRoot: true
        runAsUser: 10000

    - command:
      - sh
      - -c
      - |
        mkdir -p /shared/.ssh
        cp /secrets/id_rsa /shared/.ssh/id_rsa
        cp /secrets/known_host /shared/.ssh/known_hosts
        chmod 600 /shared/.ssh/id_rsa
        cat > /shared/.ssh/config << EOF
        Host github.com
          HostName ssh.github.com
          IdentityFile /home/atlantis/.ssh/id_rsa
          Port 443
          User git
          ServerAliveInterval 20
        EOF
      image: busybox
      name: init-ssh
      volumeMounts:
      - mountPath: /secrets
        name: ssh-key-private
      - mountPath: /shared
        name: shared-ssh
    livenessProbe:
      enabled: true
      failureThreshold: 5
      initialDelaySeconds: 5
      periodSeconds: 60
      scheme: HTTP
      successThreshold: 1
      timeoutSeconds: 5
    nodeSelector: {}
    orgAllowlist: github.com/LexisNexis-RBA/*
    podTemplate:
      annotations: null
      labels:
        require-iam-access: "true"
        require-internet-egress: "true"
    readinessProbe:
      enabled: true
      failureThreshold: 5
      initialDelaySeconds: 5
      periodSeconds: 60
      scheme: HTTP
      successThreshold: 1
      timeoutSeconds: 5
    replicaCount: 1
    repoConfig: |
      ---
      repos:
      - id: /.*/
        apply_requirements: [approved, mergeable]
    resources:
      limits:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 1Gi
      requests:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 1Gi
    service:
      port: 80
      type: NodePort
    serviceAccount:
      annotations:
        eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn: arn:aws:iam::512544833523:role/svc-icis-event-streaming-pre-live-atlantis-s3-rw
      create: true
      name: null

apiVersion: helm.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v2beta1
kind: HelmRelease
metadata:
  name: icis-github-arc-runner-scale-set
  namespace: icis-gh-arc-runners
spec:
  chart:
    spec:
      chart: gha-runner-scale-set
      sourceRef:
        kind: HelmRepository
        name: helm-charts
        namespace: flux-system
      version: 0.9.3
  interval: 5m0s
  releaseName: icis-github-arc-runner-scale-set
  upgrade:
    remediation:
      remediateLastFailure: true
      strategy: rollback
  values:
    githubConfigSecret: gh-config-sec-org-sre-eks
    githubConfigUrl: https://github.com/LexisNexis-RBA
    maxRunners: 15
    minRunners: 2
    podSecurityContext:
      fsGroup: 65533
      runAsUser: 100
    runnerGroup: dsg-icis-eks-github-actions-runner
    runnerScaleSetName: gha-runner-cha-eks-5a
    template:
      spec:
        containers:
        - command:
          - /home/runner/run.sh
          env:
          - name: DOCKER_HOST
            value: unix:///var/run/docker.sock
          image: artifacts.cha.rbxd.ds/github-actions-runner/gh-runner:2.327.1
          name: runner
          resources:
            limits:
              cpu: 300m
              memory: 512Mi
            requests:
              cpu: 100m
              memory: 256Mi
          volumeMounts:
          - mountPath: /home/runner/_work
            name: work
          - mountPath: /var/run
            name: dind-sock
        - args:
          - dockerd
          - --host=unix:///var/run/docker.sock
          - --group=$(DOCKER_GROUP_GID)
          env:
          - name: DOCKER_GROUP_GID
            value: "123"
          image: artifacts.cha.rbxd.ds/github-actions-runner/dind/docker:dind-4.0.0
          name: dind
          resources:
            limits:
              cpu: 800m
              memory: 1500Mi
            requests:
              cpu: 100m
              memory: 256Mi
          securityContext:
            privileged: true
          volumeMounts:
          - mountPath: /home/runner/_work
            name: work
          - mountPath: /var/run
            name: dind-sock
          - mountPath: /home/runner/externals
            name: dind-externals
        initContainers:
        - command:
          - cp
          - -r
          - -v
          - /home/runner/externals/.
          - /home/runner/tmpDir/
          image: artifacts.cha.rbxd.ds/github-actions-runner/gh-runner:2.327.1
          name: init-dind-externals
          securityContext:
            allowPrivilegeEscalation: true
            privileged: true
            runAsGroup: 123
            runAsUser: 1001
          volumeMounts:
          - mountPath: /home/runner/tmpDir
            name: dind-externals
        volumes:
        - emptyDir: {}
          name: work
        - emptyDir: {}
          name: dind-sock
        - emptyDir: {}
          name: dind-externals

          - mountPath: /home/runner/_work
            name: work
          - mountPath: /var/run
            name: dind-sock
          - mountPath: /home/runner/externals
            name: dind-externals
        initContainers:
        - command:
          - cp
          - -r
          - -v
          - /home/runner/externals/.
          - /home/runner/tmpDir/
          image: artifacts.cha.rbxd.ds/github-actions-runner/gh-runner:2.327.1
          name: init-dind-externals
          securityContext:
            allowPrivilegeEscalation: true
            privileged: true
            runAsGroup: 123
            runAsUser: 1001
          volumeMounts:
          - mountPath: /home/runner/tmpDir
            name: dind-externals
        volumes:
        - emptyDir: {}
          name: work
        - emptyDir: {}
          name: dind-sock
        - emptyDir: {}
          name: dind-externals

        enabled: false
        resourceNames:
        - gitlab-runner
    resources:
      limits:
        cpu: 200m
        memory: 256Mi
      requests:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 128Mi
    runnerRegistrationToken: PqsHGTe6Gmqnu4zZq4Yp
    runners:

kind: HelmRelease
metadata:
  name: icis-grafana
  namespace: icis-monitoring
spec:
  chart:
    spec:
      chart: grafana
      sourceRef:
        kind: HelmRepository
        name: grafana
        namespace: icis-monitoring
      version: 9.2.2
  interval: 5m0s
  releaseName: icis-grafana
  targetNamespace: icis-monitoring
  upgrade:
    remediation:
      remediateLastFailure: true
      strategy: rollback
  values:
    extraSecretMounts:
    - defaultMode: 292
      mountPath: /etc/secrets/db
      name: grafana-db-secret
      readOnly: true
      secretName: grafana-db-secret
    - defaultMode: 292
      mountPath: /etc/secrets/oauth
      name: grafana-sso-auth-secret
      readOnly: true
      secretName: grafana-sso-auth-secret
    grafana.ini:
      auth:
        disable_login_form: false
        disable_signout_menu: false
      auth.azuread:
        allow_sign_up: true
        api_url: https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/me
        auth_url: https://login.microsoftonline.com/$__file{/etc/secrets/oauth/tenant-id}/oauth2/v2.0/authorize
        auto_login: false
        client_id: $__file{/etc/secrets/oauth/client-id}
        client_secret_file: $__file{/etc/secrets/oauth/client-secret}
        enabled: true
        name: AzureAD
        scopes: openid email profile
        token_url: https://login.microsoftonline.com/$__file{/etc/secrets/oauth/tenant-id}/oauth2/v2.0/token
      database:
        host: $__file{/etc/secrets/db/db-host}
        name: grafana
        password: $__file{/etc/secrets/db/db-password}
        ssl_mode: disable
        type: postgres
        user: $__file{/etc/secrets/db/db-username}
      server:
        root_url: https://grafana-eks.cha.eu-west-1.dev
      smtp:
        enabled: true
        from_address: grafana-eks@cha.rbxd.ds
        from_name: ICIS Grafana CHA EKS
        host: chamailrelay.cha.rbxd.ds:25
        skip_verify: true
        startTLS_policy: NoStartTLS
    image:
      debug: true
      pullPolicy: IfNotPresent
      pullSecrets: []
      registry: artifacts.cha.rbxd.ds
      repository: custom-grafana
      tag: 12.0.1
    replicaCount: 2
    serviceAccount:
      create: false
      name: aws-services-monitoring
    serviceMonitor:
      enabled: true

spec:
  chart:
    spec:
      chart: icis-monitoring-exporter
      sourceRef:
        kind: HelmRepository
        name: helm-charts
        namespace: flux-system
      version: 1.0.1
  interval: 5m0s
  releaseName: tesla-exporter
  upgrade:
    remediation:
      remediateLastFailure: true
      strategy: rollback
  values:
    fullnameOverride: tesla-check-exporter
    image:
      pullPolicy: IfNotPresent
      repository: artifacts.cha.rbxd.ds/icis-monitoring/tesla_checks_exporter
      tag: 1.0.0
    nameOverride: tesla-check-exporter
    secrets:
    - envName: COLLECTORS_SERVERS
      key: COLLECTORS_SERVERS
      name: tesla-vars
    - envName: EXPORTSERVICES_SERVERS
      key: EXPORTSERVICES_SERVERS
      name: tesla-vars
    - envName: NORMALISERS_SERVERS
      key: NORMALISERS_SERVERS
      name: tesla-vars
    - envName: PROCESSORS_SERVERS
      key: PROCESSORS_SERVERS
      name: tesla-vars
    service:
      port: 3301
      type: ClusterIP
    serviceMonitor:
      interval: 30s
      namespace: icis-monitoring
      release: tesla-exporter
    vault:
      mount: kv/cha/k8s
      path: icis-monitoring/tesla-vars
      type: kv-v2

kind: VaultAuth
metadata:
  name: icis-monitoring-vault-secret-auth
  namespace: icis-monitoring
spec:
  kubernetes:
    role: kv-icis-monitoring-read
    serviceAccount: icis-monitoring
  method: kubernetes
  mount: cha/eks-a
---
apiVersion: secrets.hashicorp.com/v1beta1
kind: VaultStaticSecret
metadata:
  name: grafana-db-secret
  namespace: icis-monitoring
spec:
  destination:
    create: true
    name: grafana-db-secret
  mount: kv/cha/k8s
  path: icis-monitoring/grafana/database
  refreshAfter: 300s
  type: kv-v2
  vaultAuthRef: icis-monitoring-vault-secret-auth
---
apiVersion: secrets.hashicorp.com/v1beta1
kind: VaultStaticSecret
metadata:
  name: grafana-sso-auth-secret
  namespace: icis-monitoring
spec:
  destination:
    create: true
    name: grafana-sso-auth-secret
  mount: kv/cha/k8s
  path: icis-monitoring/grafana/azure-sso
  refreshAfter: 300s
  type: kv-v2
  vaultAuthRef: icis-monitoring-vault-secret-auth
---
apiVersion: secrets.hashicorp.com/v1beta1

  namespace: icis-monitoring

apiVersion: v1
data:
  consul-template-config.hcl: |-
    vault {
      renew_token = false
      vault_agent_token_file = "/home/vault/.vault-token"
      retry {
        backoff = "1s"
      }
    }

    template {
      destination = "/etc/secrets/.env"
      contents = <<EOH
      {{- with secret "kv/cha/k8s/data/icis-squidex/common"  }}
      SQUIDEX_CLIENT_ID="{{ .Data.data.identityAdminClientId }}"
      SQUIDEX_CLIENT_SECRET="{{ .Data.data.identityAdminClientSecret }}"
      {{ end }}
      EOH
    }
  vault-agent-config.hcl: |-
    # Uncomment this to have Agent run once (e.g. when running as an initContainer)
    exit_after_auth = true
    pid_file = "/home/vault/pidfile"

    auto_auth {
        method "kubernetes" {
            mount_path = "auth/cha/eks-a"
            config = {
                role = "kv-icis-squidex-read"
            }
        }

        sink "file" {
            config = {
                path = "/home/vault/.vault-token"
            }
        }
    }
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: icis-squidex-cli-config
  namespace: icis-squidex-performance
---
apiVersion: v1
data:
  consul-template-config.hcl: "vault {\n  renew_token = false\n  vault_agent_token_file
    = \"/home/vault/.vault-token\"\n  retry {\n    backoff = \"1s\"\n  }\n}\n\ntemplate
    {\n  destination = \"/etc/secrets/appsettings.secrets.json\"\n  contents = <<EOH\n
    \ {\n    \"eventStore\": {\n      \"mongoDb\": {\n        {{- with secret \"kv/cha/k8s/data/icis-squidex/common\"
    \ }}\n        \"configuration\": \"mongodb+srv://{{ .Data.data.mongoUser }}:{{
    .Data.data.mongoPassword }}@cha-pre-live-ak0n6.mongodb.net\"\n        {{ end }}\n
    \     }\n    },  \n\n    \"store\": {\n      \"mongoDb\": {\n        {{- with
    secret \"kv/cha/k8s/data/icis-squidex/common\"  }}\n        \"configuration\":
    \"mongodb+srv://{{ .Data.data.mongoUser }}:{{ .Data.data.mongoPassword }}@cha-pre-live-ak0n6.mongodb.net\"\n
    \       {{ end }}\n      }\n    },\n    \n    \"assetStore\": {\n      \"mongoDb\":
    {\n        {{- with secret \"kv/cha/k8s/data/icis-squidex/common\"  }}\n        \"configuration\":
    \"mongodb+srv://{{ .Data.data.mongoUser }}:{{ .Data.data.mongoPassword }}@cha-pre-live-ak0n6.mongodb.net\"\n
    \       {{ end }}\n      }\n    },\n\n    \"identity\": {\n      {{- with secret
    \"kv/cha/k8s/data/icis-squidex/common\"  }}\n      \"adminClientId\": \"{{ .Data.data.identityAdminClientId
    }}\",\n      \"adminClientSecret\": \"{{ .Data.data.identityAdminClientSecret
    }}\"\n      {{ end }}\n    }\n  }\n  EOH\n}  "
  vault-agent-config.hcl: |-
    # Uncomment this to have Agent run once (e.g. when running as an initContainer)
    exit_after_auth = true
    pid_file = "/home/vault/pidfile"

    auto_auth {
        method "kubernetes" {
            mount_path = "auth/cha/eks-a"
            config = {
                role = "kv-icis-squidex-read"
            }
        }

        sink "file" {
            config = {
                path = "/home/vault/.vault-token"
            }
        }
    }

    }}\",\n      \"adminClientSecret\": \"{{ .Data.data.identityAdminClientSecret
    }}\"\n      {{ end }}\n    }\n  }\n  EOH\n}  "
  vault-agent-config.hcl: |-
    # Uncomment this to have Agent run once (e.g. when running as an initContainer)
    exit_after_auth = true
    pid_file = "/home/vault/pidfile"

    auto_auth {
        method "kubernetes" {
            mount_path = "auth/cha/eks-a"
            config = {
                role = "kv-icis-squidex-read"
            }
        }

        sink "file" {
            config = {
                path = "/home/vault/.vault-token"
            }
        }
    }

metadata:
  name: icis-squidex-config
  namespace: icis-squidex-uat

  namespace: acmser-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 27015
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27015
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: UDP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 192.168.248.0/21
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-icis-monitoring
  namespace: acmser-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-acmser-systest
  namespace: acmser-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: acmser-systest
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: acmser-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: acmser-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-monitoring
  namespace: acmser-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-all
  namespace: acmser-systest
spec:
  egress: []
  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}
---

metadata:
  name: allow-egress-http-external
  namespace: cimage-staging
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 80
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-mongodb
  namespace: cimage-staging
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 27015
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27015
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: UDP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 192.168.248.0/21
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-redis
  namespace: cimage-staging
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 6379
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 10.52.36.0/22
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-icis-monitoring
  namespace: cimage-staging
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-cimage-staging
  namespace: cimage-staging
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: cimage-staging
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: cimage-staging
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---

---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-all
  namespace: cimage-staging
spec:
  egress: []
  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}
---

kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: darchk-dev
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: darchk-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: darchk-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-monitoring
  namespace: darchk-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-all
  namespace: darchk-systest
spec:
  egress: []
  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-datapr-integration
  namespace: datapr-integration
spec:
  egress:
  - to:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: datapr-integration
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-http-external
  namespace: datapr-integration
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 80
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-sql-server
  namespace: datapr-integration
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 3306
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-icis-monitoring
  namespace: datapr-integration
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-datapr-integration
  namespace: datapr-integration
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: datapr-integration
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-confluent
  namespace: didens-integration
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 9092
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 172.16.0.0/16
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-didens-integration
  namespace: didens-integration
spec:
  egress:
  - to:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: didens-integration
  podSelector: {}
---

      protocol: TCP
    - port: 80
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-mongodb
  namespace: didens-integration
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 27015
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27015
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: UDP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 192.168.248.0/21
  podSelector: {}
---

  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-grn-performance
  namespace: grn-performance
spec:
  egress:
  - to:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: grn-performance
  podSelector: {}
---

  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 80
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-icis-monitoring
  namespace: icis-squidex-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-egress-stash
  namespace: icis-squidex-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 22
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 8080
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 10.52.32.70/32
  - ports:
    - port: 22
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 8080
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 10.52.32.0/21
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-icis-squidex-systest
  namespace: icis-squidex-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-squidex-systest
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: icis-squidex-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: icis-squidex-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-monitoring
  namespace: icis-squidex-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-all
  namespace: icis-squidex-systest
spec:
  egress: []
  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-confluent
  namespace: icis-squidex-uat
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 9092
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 172.16.0.0/16
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-http-external
  namespace: icis-squidex-uat
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 80
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-icis-squidex-uat

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-mongodb
  namespace: icis-squidex-uat
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 27015
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27015
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: UDP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 192.168.248.0/21
  podSelector: {}

  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: petana-performance
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: petana-performance
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: petana-performance
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1

spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}

kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-pforecast-performance
  namespace: pforecast-performance
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: pforecast-performance
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: pforecast-performance
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: pforecast-performance
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-monitoring
  namespace: pforecast-performance
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-all
  namespace: pforecast-performance
spec:
  egress: []
  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-confluent
  namespace: pforecast-staging
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 9092
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 172.16.0.0/16
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-http-external
  namespace: pforecast-staging
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 80
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-mongodb
  namespace: pforecast-staging

  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 27015
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27015
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: UDP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 192.168.248.0/21
  podSelector: {}
---

  namespace: priceopt-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-priceopt-systest
  namespace: priceopt-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: priceopt-systest
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: priceopt-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: priceopt-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1

        matchLabels:
          name: monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:

  podSelector: {}

  name: default-deny-all
  namespace: priceopt-systest
spec:
  egress: []
  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-all
  namespace: sbfeed-staging
spec:
  egress: []
  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-confluent
  namespace: sbfeed-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 9092
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 172.16.0.0/16
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-http-external
  namespace: sbfeed-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 80
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-mongodb
  namespace: sbfeed-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 27015
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 27015
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27016
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 27017
      protocol: UDP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 192.168.248.0/21
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-sbfeed-systest
  namespace: sbfeed-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - to:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: sbfeed-systest
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-icis-monitoring
  namespace: sbfeed-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-sbfeed-systest
  namespace: sbfeed-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: sbfeed-systest
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: sbfeed-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: sbfeed-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-monitoring

spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}

kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-icis-monitoring
  namespace: sbnews-performance
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-gitlab-runner
  namespace: sbnews-performance
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-gitlab-runner
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-sbnews-performance
  namespace: sbnews-performance
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: sbnews-performance
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: sbnews-performance
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: sbnews-performance
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-monitoring
  namespace: sbnews-performance
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-all
  namespace: sbnews-performance
spec:
  egress: []
  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-confluent
  namespace: sbnews-staging
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 9092
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 172.16.0.0/16
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-http-external
  namespace: sbnews-staging
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 80
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---

kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-sboutg-systest
  namespace: sboutg-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - to:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: sboutg-systest
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-icis-monitoring
  namespace: sboutg-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress-sboutg-systest
  namespace: sboutg-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: sboutg-systest
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: icis-ingress
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-dns
  namespace: sboutg-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 53
      protocol: UDP
    - port: 53
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-internet-egress
  namespace: sboutg-systest
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-internet-egress: "true"
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-allow-monitoring
  namespace: sboutg-systest
spec:
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          name: monitoring
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: prometheus
  podSelector: {}
---
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-all
  namespace: sboutg-systest
spec:
  egress: []
  ingress: []
  podSelector: {}
---

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-egress-confluent
  namespace: spfeed-performance
spec:
  egress:
  - ports:
    - port: 443
      protocol: TCP
    - port: 9092
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 172.16.0.0/16
  podSelector: {}
---

    - port: 8181
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 10.52.160.0/24
  - ports:
    - port: 8181
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 10.52.161.0/24
  - ports:
    - port: 8181
      protocol: TCP
    to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 10.52.162.0/24
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      require-iam-access: "true"

  method: kubernetes

metadata:
  name: rundeck-database-secret
  namespace: rundeck-dev
spec:
  destination:
    create: true
    name: rundeck-database-secret
  mount: kv/cha/k8s
  path: rundeck/rundeck-database-secret
  refreshAfter: 300s
  type: kv-v2
  vaultAuthRef: rundeck-vault-secret-auth
---

apiVersion: helm.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v2beta1
kind: HelmRelease
metadata:
  name: apm-server
  namespace: genesis-platform
spec:
  chart:
    spec:
      chart: apm-server
      sourceRef:
        kind: HelmRepository
        name: elastic
        namespace: genesis-platform
      version: 7.17.3
  interval: 5m0s
  upgrade:
    remediation:
      remediateLastFailure: true
      strategy: rollback
  values:
    apmConfig:
      apm-server.yml: |
        apm-server:
          host: "0.0.0.0:8200"
          rum.enabled: true
          rum.event_rate.limit: 300
          rum.event_rate.lru_size: 1000
        queue:
          mem:
            events: 40000
        output.elasticsearch:
          username: '${ELASTICSEARCH_USERNAME}'
          password: '${ELASTICSEARCH_PASSWORD}'
          protocol: https
          hosts: ["elasticsearch-master:9200"]
          bulk_max_size: 10000
          worker: 4
          ssl.certificate_authorities:
            - /usr/share/apm-server/config/certs/elastic-certificate.pem
    extraEnvs:
    - name: ELASTICSEARCH_USERNAME
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          key: username
          name: elastic-credentials
    - name: ELASTICSEARCH_PASSWORD
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          key: password
          name: elastic-credentials
    imageTag: 7.17.3
    ingress:
      annotations:
        cert-manager.io/cluster-issuer: vault-issuer
        external-dns.alpha.kubernetes.io/hostname: apm.eks-4.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
        lnrs.io/zone-type: private
      className: icis-nginx-ingress
      enabled: true
      hosts:
      - apm.eks-4.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
      - apm.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
      path: /
      tls:
      - hosts:
        - apm.eks-4.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
        secretName: apmserver-genesis.cha-eu-west-1-dev
      - hosts:
        - apm.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
        secretName: apmserver-old-genesis.cha-eu-west-1-dev
    replicas: 3
    resources:
      limits:
        cpu: 1000m
        memory: 2Gi
      requests:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 1Gi
    secretMounts:
    - name: elastic-certificate-pem
      path: /usr/share/apm-server/config/certs
      secretName: elastic-certificate-pem
---
apiVersion: helm.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v2beta1
kind: HelmRelease
metadata:
  name: elasticsearch
  namespace: genesis-platform
spec:
  chart:
    spec:
      chart: elasticsearch
      sourceRef:
        kind: HelmRepository
        name: elastic
        namespace: genesis-platform
      version: 7.17.3
  interval: 5m0s
  upgrade:
    remediation:
      remediateLastFailure: true
      strategy: rollback
  values:
    antiAffinity: soft
    clusterHealthCheckParams: wait_for_status=yellow&timeout=1s
    esConfig:
      elasticsearch.yml: |
        xpack.security.enabled: true
        xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true
        xpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode: certificate
        xpack.security.transport.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-certificates.p12
        xpack.security.transport.ssl.truststore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-certificates.p12
        xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true
        xpack.security.http.ssl.truststore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-certificates.p12
        xpack.security.http.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-certificates.p12
    esJavaOpts: -Xmx2g -Xms2g
    extraEnvs:
    - name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          key: password
          name: elastic-credentials
    imageTag: 7.17.3
    ingress:
      annotations:
        cert-manager.io/cluster-issuer: vault-issuer
        external-dns.alpha.kubernetes.io/hostname: elasticsearch.eks-4.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
        lnrs.io/zone-type: private
        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/backend-protocol: HTTPS
      className: icis-nginx-ingress
      enabled: true
      hosts:
      - elasticsearch.eks-4.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
      path: /
      tls:
      - hosts:
        - elasticsearch.eks-4.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
        secretName: elasticsearch-genesis.cha-eu-west-1-dev
    protocol: https
    replicas: 3
    resources:
      limits:
        cpu: 2000m
        memory: 4Gi
      requests:
        cpu: 1000m
        memory: 4Gi
    roles:
      data: "true"
      ingest: "true"
      master: "true"
    secretMounts:
    - name: elastic-certificates
      path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs
      secretName: elastic-certificates
    volumeClaimTemplate:
      accessModes:
      - ReadWriteOnce
      resources:
        requests:
          storage: 450Gi
      storageClassName: ebs-gp3-ext4-retain
---
apiVersion: helm.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v2beta1
kind: HelmRelease
metadata:
  name: kibana
  namespace: genesis-platform
spec:
  chart:
    spec:
      chart: kibana
      sourceRef:
        kind: HelmRepository
        name: elastic
        namespace: genesis-platform
      version: 7.17.3
  interval: 5m0s
  upgrade:
    remediation:
      remediateLastFailure: true
      strategy: rollback
  values:
    elasticsearchHosts: https://elasticsearch-master:9200
    extraEnvs:
    - name: ELASTICSEARCH_USERNAME
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          key: username
          name: elastic-credentials
    - name: ELASTICSEARCH_PASSWORD
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          key: password
          name: elastic-credentials
    - name: KIBANA_ENCRYPTION_KEY
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          key: encryptionkey
          name: kibana
    imageTag: 7.17.3
    ingress:
      annotations:
        cert-manager.io/cluster-issuer: vault-issuer
        external-dns.alpha.kubernetes.io/hostname: kibana.eks-4.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
        lnrs.io/zone-type: private
        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/backend-protocol: HTTPS
      className: icis-nginx-ingress
      enabled: true
      hosts:
      - kibana.eks-4.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
      path: /
      tls:
      - hosts:
        - kibana.eks-4.genesis.cha.eu-west-1.dev
        secretName: kibana-genesis.cha-eu-west-1-dev
    kibanaConfig:
      kibana.yml: |
        server.ssl:
          enabled: true
          key: /usr/share/kibana/config/certs/elastic-certificate.pem
          certificate: /usr/share/kibana/config/certs/elastic-certificate.pem
        xpack.security.encryptionKey: ${KIBANA_ENCRYPTION_KEY}
        xpack.encryptedSavedObjects.encryptionKey: ${KIBANA_ENCRYPTION_KEY}
        elasticsearch.ssl:
          certificateAuthorities: /usr/share/kibana/config/certs/elastic-certificate.pem
          verificationMode: certificate
    protocol: https
    replicas: 2
    secretMounts:
    - name: elastic-certificate-pem
      path: /usr/share/kibana/config/certs
      secretName: elastic-certificate-pem
---
apiVersion: kafka.strimzi.io/v1beta2
kind: KafkaConnector
metadata:
  labels:
    strimzi.io/cluster: prelive-connect-cluster
  name: adchrt-integration-subscription-product-items
  namespace: icis-event-streaming
spec:
  class: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.MongoSinkConnector
  config:
    collection: product_items
    config.action.reload: restart
    connection.uri: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/adchrt-mongo-uri/mongoConnection:connectionURI}
    database: adchrt-integration
    document.id.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.id.strategy.ProvidedInValueStrategy
    errors.log.enable: true
    errors.log.include.messages: true
    errors.retry.delay.max.ms: 60000
    errors.retry.timeout: 3
    key.converter: org.apache.kafka.connect.storage.StringConverter
    key.converter.schemas.enable: false
    topics: public_uat_subscription_product_items_1
    transforms: RenameField
    transforms.RenameField.renames: id:_id
    transforms.RenameField.type: org.apache.kafka.connect.transforms.ReplaceField$Value
    value.converter: io.confluent.connect.avro.AvroConverter
    value.converter.basic.auth.credentials.source: USER_INFO
    value.converter.basic.auth.user.info: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:password}
    value.converter.schema.registry.url: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:url}
    value.converter.schemas.enable: false
  tasksMax: 2
---

    strimzi.io/cluster: prelive-connect-cluster
  name: adchrt-staging-subscription-product-items
  namespace: icis-event-streaming
spec:
  class: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.MongoSinkConnector
  config:
    collection: product_items
    config.action.reload: restart
    connection.uri: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/adchrt-mongo-uri/mongoConnection:connectionURI}
    database: adchrt-staging
    document.id.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.id.strategy.ProvidedInValueStrategy
    errors.log.enable: true

apiVersion: kafka.strimzi.io/v1beta2
kind: KafkaConnector
metadata:
  labels:
    strimzi.io/cluster: prelive-connect-cluster
  name: price-forecast-staging-refdata-mappings
  namespace: icis-event-streaming
spec:
  class: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.MongoSinkConnector
  config:
    collection: refdata.order.mappings
    config.action.reload: restart
    connection.uri: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/price-forecast-mongo-uri/mongoConnection:connectionURI}
    database: pf-staging
    document.id.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.id.strategy.ProvidedInValueStrategy
    errors.log.enable: true
    errors.log.include.messages: true
    errors.retry.delay.max.ms: 60000
    errors.retry.timeout: 3
    key.converter: org.apache.kafka.connect.storage.StringConverter
    key.converter.schemas.enable: false
    topics: public_uat_refdata_mappings_1
    transforms: RenameField,FilterValue
    transforms.FilterValue.filter.condition: $[?(@.data_producer_entity_class in ['icis.iddn.commodity',
      'icis.iddn.location'])]
    transforms.FilterValue.filter.type: include
    transforms.FilterValue.type: io.confluent.connect.transforms.Filter$Value
    transforms.RenameField.renames: id:_id
    transforms.RenameField.type: org.apache.kafka.connect.transforms.ReplaceField$Value
    value.converter: io.confluent.connect.avro.AvroConverter
    value.converter.basic.auth.credentials.source: USER_INFO
    value.converter.basic.auth.user.info: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:password}
    value.converter.schema.registry.url: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:url}
    value.converter.schemas.enable: false
  tasksMax: 2

apiVersion: kafka.strimzi.io/v1beta2
kind: KafkaConnector
metadata:
  labels:
    strimzi.io/cluster: prelive-connect-cluster
  name: pricing-performance-energy-basis-specifications
  namespace: icis-event-streaming
spec:
  class: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.MongoSinkConnector
  config:
    collection: energy_basis_specifications_1
    config.action.reload: restart
    connection.uri: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/pricing-mongo-uri/mongoConnection:connectionURI}
    database: pricing-performance
    document.id.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.id.strategy.ProvidedInValueStrategy
    errors.log.enable: true
    errors.log.include.messages: true
    errors.retry.delay.max.ms: 60000
    errors.retry.timeout: -1
    key.converter: org.apache.kafka.connect.storage.StringConverter
    key.converter.schemas.enable: false
    post.processor.chain: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.BlockListValueProjector
    topics: public_uat_energy_basis_price_assessments_specifications_1

kind: KafkaConnector
metadata:
  labels:
    strimzi.io/cluster: prelive-connect-cluster
  name: pricing-performance-pricing-petchem-ref-period
  namespace: icis-event-streaming
spec:
  class: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.MongoSinkConnector
  config:
    collection: petchem_period_1
    config.action.reload: restart
    connection.uri: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/pricing-mongo-uri/mongoConnection:connectionURI}
    database: pricing-performance
    document.id.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.id.strategy.ProvidedInValueStrategy
    errors.log.enable: true
    errors.log.include.messages: true
    errors.retry.delay.max.ms: 60000
    errors.retry.timeout: -1
    key.converter: org.apache.kafka.connect.storage.StringConverter
    key.converter.schemas.enable: false
    topics: public_uat_petchem_period_1
    transforms: RenameField
    transforms.RenameField.renames: id:_id
    transforms.RenameField.type: org.apache.kafka.connect.transforms.ReplaceField$Value
    value.converter: io.confluent.connect.avro.AvroConverter
    value.converter.basic.auth.credentials.source: USER_INFO
    value.converter.basic.auth.user.info: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:password}
    value.converter.schema.registry.url: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:url}
    value.converter.schemas.enable: false
  tasksMax: 6
---

apiVersion: kafka.strimzi.io/v1beta2
kind: KafkaConnector
metadata:
  labels:
    strimzi.io/cluster: prelive-connect-cluster
  name: pricing-staging-energy-basis-prices-corrections
  namespace: icis-event-streaming
spec:
  class: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.MongoSinkConnector
  config:
    collection: energy_basis_1
    config.action.reload: restart
    connection.uri: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/pricing-mongo-uri/mongoConnection:connectionURI}
    database: pricing-staging
    document.id.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.id.strategy.ProvidedInKeyStrategy
    document.id.strategy.overwrite.existing: true
    errors.log.enable: true
    errors.log.include.messages: true
    errors.retry.delay.max.ms: 60000
    errors.retry.timeout: -1
    key.converter: org.apache.kafka.connect.storage.StringConverter
    key.converter.schemas.enable: false
    topics: public_uat_energy_basis_price_assessments_2
    transforms: hk
    transforms.hk.field: _id
    transforms.hk.type: org.apache.kafka.connect.transforms.HoistField$Key
    value.converter: io.confluent.connect.avro.AvroConverter
    value.converter.basic.auth.credentials.source: USER_INFO
    value.converter.basic.auth.user.info: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:password}
    value.converter.schema.registry.url: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:url}
    value.converter.schemas.enable: false
    writemodel.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.writemodel.strategy.UpdateOneTimestampsStrategy
  tasksMax: 6
---
apiVersion: kafka.strimzi.io/v1beta2
kind: KafkaConnector
metadata:
  labels:
    strimzi.io/cluster: prelive-connect-cluster
  name: pricing-staging-energy-basis-specifications
  namespace: icis-event-streaming
spec:
  class: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.MongoSinkConnector
  config:
    collection: energy_basis_specifications_1
    config.action.reload: restart
    connection.uri: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/pricing-mongo-uri/mongoConnection:connectionURI}
    database: pricing-staging
    document.id.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.id.strategy.ProvidedInValueStrategy
    errors.log.enable: true
    errors.log.include.messages: true
    errors.retry.delay.max.ms: 60000
    errors.retry.timeout: -1
    key.converter: org.apache.kafka.connect.storage.StringConverter
    key.converter.schemas.enable: false
    post.processor.chain: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.BlockListValueProjector
    topics: public_uat_energy_basis_price_assessments_specifications_1
    transforms: headerToField,patternRename
    transforms.headerToField.header.mappings: id:STRING
    transforms.headerToField.type: com.github.jcustenborder.kafka.connect.transform.common.HeaderToField$Value
    transforms.patternRename.field.pattern: ^id$
    transforms.patternRename.field.replacement: _id
    transforms.patternRename.type: com.github.jcustenborder.kafka.connect.transform.common.PatternRename$Value
    value.converter: io.confluent.connect.avro.AvroConverter
    value.converter.basic.auth.credentials.source: USER_INFO
    value.converter.basic.auth.user.info: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:password}
    value.converter.schema.registry.url: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:url}
    value.converter.schemas.enable: false
    value.projection.list: metadata.created_for
    value.projection.type: BlockList
    writemodel.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.writemodel.strategy.UpdateOneTimestampsStrategy
  tasksMax: 6
---

apiVersion: kafka.strimzi.io/v1beta2
kind: KafkaConnector
metadata:
  labels:
    strimzi.io/cluster: prelive-connect-cluster
  name: pricing-staging-energy-ref-currencies
  namespace: icis-event-streaming
spec:
  class: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.MongoSinkConnector
  config:
    collection: energy_ref_currencies_1
    config.action.reload: restart
    connection.uri: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/pricing-mongo-uri/mongoConnection:connectionURI}
    database: pricing-staging
    document.id.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.id.strategy.ProvidedInValueStrategy
    errors.log.enable: true
    errors.log.include.messages: true
    errors.retry.delay.max.ms: 60000
    errors.retry.timeout: -1
    key.converter: org.apache.kafka.connect.storage.StringConverter
    key.converter.schemas.enable: false
    post.processor.chain: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.processor.BlockListValueProjector
    topics: public_uat_energy_currencies_1
    transforms: headerToField,patternRename
    transforms.headerToField.header.mappings: id:STRING
    transforms.headerToField.type: com.github.jcustenborder.kafka.connect.transform.common.HeaderToField$Value
    transforms.patternRename.field.pattern: ^id$
    transforms.patternRename.field.replacement: _id
    transforms.patternRename.type: com.github.jcustenborder.kafka.connect.transform.common.PatternRename$Value
    value.converter: io.confluent.connect.avro.AvroConverter
    value.converter.basic.auth.credentials.source: USER_INFO
    value.converter.basic.auth.user.info: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:password}
    value.converter.schema.registry.url: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:url}
    value.converter.schemas.enable: false
    value.projection.list: metadata.created_for
    value.projection.type: BlockList
    writemodel.strategy: com.mongodb.kafka.connect.sink.writemodel.strategy.UpdateOneTimestampsStrategy
  tasksMax: 6
---

apiVersion: kafka.strimzi.io/v1beta2
kind: KafkaConnector
metadata:
  labels:
    strimzi.io/cluster: prelive-connect-cluster
  name: sboutg-performance-outage-snd
  namespace: icis-event-streaming
spec:
  class: io.confluent.connect.jdbc.JdbcSourceConnector
  config:
    catalog.pattern: SupplyNDemandEditing
    config.action.reload: restart
    connection.password: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/sboutg-sql-connect/sqlconnection:password}
    connection.url: jdbc:sqlserver://CHAEWADBST010V.cha.rbxd.ds:1433;databaseName=SupplyNDemandEditing
    connection.user: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/sboutg-sql-connect/sqlconnection:username}
    connector.class: io.confluent.connect.jdbc.JdbcSourceConnector
    dialect.name: SqlServerDatabaseDialect
    errors.log.enable: true
    errors.log.include.messages: true
    errors.retry.delay.max.ms: 60000
    errors.retry.timeout: 3
    incrementing.column.name: outageRecordId
    key.converter: org.apache.kafka.connect.storage.StringConverter
    key.converter.basic.auth.credentials.source: USER_INFO
    key.converter.basic.auth.user.info: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:password}
    key.converter.schema.registry.url: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:url}
    key.converter.schemas.enable: false
    mode: timestamp+incrementing
    numeric.mapping: best_fit
    poll.interval.ms: 60000
    producer.override.bootstrap.servers: pkc-l568n.eu-west-1.aws.confluent.cloud:9092
    producer.override.sasl.jaas.config: org.apache.kafka.common.security.plain.PlainLoginModule
      required username='${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/kafka-secret-sboutg/kafka-secret-sboutg:kafka_user}'
      password='${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/kafka-secret-sboutg/kafka-secret-sboutg:kafka_key}';
    producer.override.sasl.mechanism: PLAIN
    producer.override.security.protocol: SASL_SSL
    query: select     top 100 * from     (         SELECT             max(ov.OutageID)
      as OutageId,             ov.ID as outageRecordId,             max(cast(ov.EditedDate
      as datetime2)) as UpdatedOn,             max(pp.PhysicalPlantID) as PhysicalPlantID,             max(cast(ov.IsForceMajeureDeclared
      as int)) as IsForceMajeureDeclared,             max(ov.ForceMajeureEndDate)
      as ForceMajeureEndDate,             max(ov.ForceMajeureStartDate) as ForceMajeureStartDate,             max(oist.Description)
      as OutageInformationSourceType,             max(ort.Description) as ReasonType,             max(orr.Description)
      as Reason,             string_agg(CONVERT(VARCHAR(max), ovc.Comment), '|-|')
      as Comment,             string_agg(CONVERT(VARCHAR(max), ovn.URL), '|-|') as
      relatedNews,             string_agg(CONCAT(oist.id, '#', CONVERT(VARCHAR(max),
      ovdp.EndDateStart)), '|-|') as EndDateStart,             string_agg(CONCAT(oist.id,
      '#', CONVERT(VARCHAR(max), ovdp.EndDateEnd)), '|-|') as EndDateEnd,             string_agg(                 CONCAT(oist.id,
      '#', CONVERT(VARCHAR(max), ovdp.StartDateStart)),                 '|-|'             )
      as StartDateStart,             string_agg(CONCAT(oist.id, '#', CONVERT(VARCHAR(max),
      ovdp.StartDateEnd)), '|-|') as StartDateEnd,             string_agg(                 CONCAT(oist.id,
      '#', CONVERT(VARCHAR(max), ovdp.OutagePercentage)),                 '|-|'             )
      as OutagePercentage,             string_agg(CONCAT(oist.id, '#', CONVERT(VARCHAR(max),
      ovdp.PlantID)), '|-|') as PlantId         FROM             [SupplyNDemandEditing].[STDC].OutageVersion
      ov WITH (NOLOCK)             left join [SupplyNDemandEditing].[STDC].OutageVersionDetail
      ovd WITH (NOLOCK) on ovd.OutageVersionID = ov.ID             left join [SupplyNDemandEditing].[ENUM].OutageInformationSourceType
      oist WITH (NOLOCK) on oist.ID = ovd.OutageInformationSourceTypeID             left
      join [SupplyNDemandEditing].[STDC].OutageVersionComment ovc on ovc.OutageVersionID
      = ov.ID             left join [SupplyNDemandEditing].[STDC].OutageVersionNews
      ovn WITH (NOLOCK) on ovn.OutageVersionID = ov.ID             left join [SupplyNDemandEditing].[STDC].OutageReason
      orr WITH (NOLOCK) on orr.ID = ovd.OutageReasonID             left join [SupplyNDemandEditing].[ENUM].OutageReasonType
      ort WITH (NOLOCK) on ort.ID = orr.OutageReasonTypeId             left join [SupplyNDemandEditing].[STDC].OutageVersionDetailPlant
      ovdp WITH (NOLOCK) on ovdp.OutageVersionDetailID = ovd.ID             left join
      [SupplyNDemandEditing].[dbo].Plant pp WITH (NOLOCK) on pp.id = ovdp.PlantID         where             ovdp.EndDateEnd
      is not null             and ovdp.StartDateStart is not null             and
      ov.EditedDate > CAST(DATEADD(month, -1, GETDATE()) AS Date)         group by             ov.ID     )
      as test
    schema.pattern: IDDN
    table.whitelist: ""
    tasks.max: 1
    timestamp.column.name: UpdatedOn
    timestamp.initial: 0
    topic.prefix: private_performance_supplydemand_outage_poc_outage_input_1
    transforms: createKey,removeId,extractId,headerId,headerPartitionKey
    transforms.createKey.fields: outageRecordId
    transforms.createKey.type: org.apache.kafka.connect.transforms.ValueToKey
    transforms.extractId.field: outageRecordId
    transforms.extractId.type: org.apache.kafka.connect.transforms.ExtractField$Key
    transforms.headerId.fields: outageRecordId
    transforms.headerId.headers: outageRecordId
    transforms.headerId.operation: copy
    transforms.headerId.type: org.apache.kafka.connect.transforms.HeaderFrom$Value
    transforms.headerPartitionKey.fields: outageRecordId
    transforms.headerPartitionKey.headers: partition_key
    transforms.headerPartitionKey.operation: copy
    transforms.headerPartitionKey.type: org.apache.kafka.connect.transforms.HeaderFrom$Value
    transforms.removeId.blacklist: increment_id
    transforms.removeId.type: org.apache.kafka.connect.transforms.ReplaceField$Value
    value.converter: io.confluent.connect.avro.AvroConverter
    value.converter.basic.auth.credentials.source: USER_INFO
    value.converter.basic.auth.user.info: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:password}
    value.converter.schema.registry.url: ${file:/opt/kafka/external-configuration/schema-registry/schemaRegistry:url}
  tasksMax: 1
